Complex type restricting another complex type, where both types contain the same
attribute. The base specifies use=required, but the derived type specifies
use=prohibited (preventing the attribute from appearing in the {attribute uses}
property computed for the derived type).

=================================== PROGRAM ====================================
testxmlschema
==================================== INPUT =====================================
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<xsd:schema xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <xsd:complexType name="ct1">
    <xsd:attribute name="attribute1" use="required"/>
  </xsd:complexType>
  <xsd:complexType name="ct2">
    <xsd:complexContent>
      <xsd:restriction base="ct1">
        <xsd:attribute name="attribute1" use="prohibited"/>
      </xsd:restriction>
    </xsd:complexContent>
  </xsd:complexType>
</xsd:schema>
==================================== OUTPUT ====================================
runtests.tmp/input.xml:6: error derivation-ok-restriction.3: Attribute attribute1 cannot be declared as prohibited, because it is declared as required by base type ct1
